Switches, Routers, Hubs

Topology and understaing of Network devices:

The Switches bundle the local PCs together. 
Computers inside Lab 1 can talk to each other through Switch 1 instantly using their hardware MAC addresses. 
They don't need the router for local chatting.

The Router sits at the border. If a PC in Lab 1 wants to talk to a PC in Lab B, the data travels up to Switch 1, 
realizes the destination is in a different room, and hands it to the Router. The Router then passes it down to Switch 2.

As of 2026, Hubs almost never implemented in real life because they are obsolete and insecure.
